      "id": "1",
      "title": "Raptaioi, Evia – The Midnight Air-Spirit Wolf",
      "slug": "lykos-aerika-mesanyhta-raptaioi",
      "author": "Titos Giochalas",
      "date": "2002-01-01",
      "excerpt": "A shepherd tale from Raptaioi where a spectral “Wolf” tears through the flock at midnight. Only heard and felt, never seen, the entity is treated with fear and immobility at the stroke of twelve.",
      "locationTags": [
        "Raptaioi - Evia"
      ],
      "mainArea": "Evia",
      "subLocation": "Raptaioi",
      "lat": 38.24649,
      "lng": 24.20174,
      "image": {
        "src": "/images/laografia/lykos-aerika-raptaioi.webp",
        "alt": "The spectral wolf of the Aerika at midnight, Raptaioi"
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "value": "Villagers spoke of a “Wolf” that appeared out of nowhere and tore at the flock. They never truly saw it—only heard and felt its presence. At midnight especially, shepherds would freeze in place, convinced the hour belonged to the Aerika."
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "value": "One elder would say, “Something just passed through the herd. It’s the Wolf.” Moving at twelve was forbidden; you stayed still, no matter the sounds, because it was the spirit’s hour."
        }
      ],
      "sources": [
        {
          "type": "book",
          "name": "Titos Giochalas",
          "title": "Evia Ta Arvanitika, Patakis",
          "year": "2002",
          "pages": "231"
        }
      ],
