    {
      "id": "310",
      "title": "The Air Spirits of Nigrita",
      "slug": "ta-aerika-tis-nigritas",
      "author": "George Frederick Abbott",
      "date": "1903",
      "excerpt": "Nigrita locals blamed chronic illness on the Aerika (air spirits). An elder woman refused medical help for her lingering fever, convinced only the Aerika were responsible.",
      "mainArea": "Serres",
      "subLocation": "Nigrita",
      "locationTags": [
        "Nigrita",
        "Serres",
        "Macedonia",
        "Aerika",
        "Aerika",
        "folk healing",
        "chronic illness"
      ],
      "lat": 40.905,
      "lng": 23.4994,
      "image": {
        "src": "/images/laografia/ta-aerika-tis-nigritas.webp",
        "alt": "Elderly woman in Nigrita speaking about the Aerika"
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "value": "In the same area I met several people who attributed their ailments to the malice of the Air Spirits. An elderly woman complained about a year-long fever; when asked about a doctor, she replied, “What can doctors do? It’s an Aeriko—medicine does nothing to them.”"
        }
