        "alt": "Whirlwind in rural Macedonia known as anemosplada"
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "value": "Locals whisper “Alexander the Great lives and reigns” when a whirlwind—called anemosplada—spins past. The word combines wind with the ancient term for dust (spodos), a nod found in Herodotus."
        }
      ],
